    "dynamic_rich_text_YQkncT": {
      "type": "dynamic-rich-text",
      "name": "t:sections.rich_text.presets.rich_text.name",
      "settings": {
        "width": "full-width",
        "title": "",
        "text": "<h2>What Is a Vehicle Center Console?</h2><p>A center console in a car is the compartment that sits between the driver and passenger seats. In a personal vehicle, it usually holds cup holders, storage, and the gear selector. In a work vehicle, that same space becomes prime real estate for mission-critical hardware. A purpose-built vehicle center console replaces or supplements the factory unit with a rigid mounting platform designed to carry heavy electronics through years of hard shifts, high vibration, and constant in-and-out use.</p><p>The difference between a stock console and a professional one comes down to engineering. Our consoles are built from high-grade aluminum and steel with powder-coated finishes, so they hold up in the high-temperature, high-vibration conditions where a molded plastic tray would crack, rattle, or work loose.</p><h2>Emergency Vehicle Consoles Built for Real Work</h2><p>An emergency vehicle console has one job: keep essential equipment secure, reachable, and safe. Loose gear becomes a projectile during sudden stops or a pursuit, and buried equipment costs officers and medics precious seconds. A properly outfitted console solves both problems at once by giving every device a fixed, ergonomic home.</p><p>Most of our consoles offer generous internal mounting space, commonly 17\" to 30\", for docking stations, siren amplifiers, printers, and control heads. Many models integrate wiring raceways and cable pass-throughs so wiring stays hidden and protected. Pair a console with the right<a href=\"https://strobesnmore.com/collections/switches-controllers\"> <span style=\"text-decoration:underline\">switch panels and controllers</span></a> and a set of<a href=\"https://strobesnmore.com/collections/sirens-speakers\"> <span style=\"text-decoration:underline\">siren and speaker systems</span></a>, and you've built a genuine in-cab workstation instead of a loose pile of add-ons.</p><p>Fire apparatus, ambulances, and utility trucks put the same demands on a console as a patrol car: constant vibration, long duty cycles, and equipment that has to stay put. Standardizing on a single console platform across a fleet also simplifies training and maintenance, because every operator finds their radio, siren head, and mounts in the same place regardless of which unit they're assigned to that shift.</p><h2>Police Center Consoles & Law Enforcement Fit</h2><p>A police center console has to account for the realities of a patrol vehicle: column shifters, OEM floor contours, and laptop docking. That is why our law enforcement consoles are engineered model by model. A Dodge Charger Police Package console, for example, uses the existing OEM floor mounts for a no-drill install and leaves clearance for a column shifter, while a Ford Interceptor Utility angled console positions a laptop at a comfortable working angle for report writing and dispatch.</p><p>For departments building out full patrol vehicles, the console is only one piece of the puzzle. Explore our wider range of<a href=\"https://strobesnmore.com/collections/law-enforcement\"> <span style=\"text-decoration:underline\">law enforcement equipment</span></a> and<a href=\"https://strobesnmore.com/collections/law-enforcement-police-lights\"> <span style=\"text-decoration:underline\">police warning lights</span></a> to coordinate the interior and exterior of the vehicle in a single order, and equip ambulances and rescue units from our<a href=\"https://strobesnmore.com/collections/fire-ems\"> <span style=\"text-decoration:underline\">fire and EMS collection</span></a>.</p><h3>Vehicle-Specific vs. Universal Consoles</h3><p>There are two ways to add a console to a fleet vehicle. A vehicle-specific console is molded and pre-drilled to match one platform, delivering the tightest, most factory-like fit with the least installation labor. A universal console, by contrast, is height-adjustable and flexible enough to serve mixed fleets or vehicles that don't have a dedicated part yet.</p><p>If you run a single make and model, vehicle-specific is almost always the better investment: less install time, a cleaner look, and better use of the space you have. If you manage a varied fleet with pickups, SUVs, and sedans, a universal solution keeps your parts list short and your techs moving. Not sure which route fits? Our team can spec it with you before you spend a dollar.</p><h3>Console Styles, Sizes & Accessories</h3><p>Consoles aren't one-size-fits-all, and neither is the way you build them out. Depending on the vehicle and the equipment load, you can choose from several form factors, each solving a different problem in the cab.</p><p>Angled models tilt the mounting surface toward the operator for better laptop and control-head visibility; browse our<a href=\"https://strobesnmore.com/collections/angled-series-consoles\"> <span style=\"text-decoration:underline\">angled series consoles</span></a> for options across popular platforms. When a crew carries extra hardware, our<a href=\"https://strobesnmore.com/collections/wide-vehicle-specific-consoles\"> <span style=\"text-decoration:underline\">wide-body console options</span></a> add lateral mounting room without crowding the driver. The VSX line blends a steel frame with lightweight polycarbonate for a strong yet lighter build, available in the<a href=\"https://strobesnmore.com/collections/vsx-vehicle-specific-consoles\"> <span style=\"text-decoration:underline\">VSX vehicle-specific consoles</span></a> range, while low-profile layouts suit cabs where legroom and sightlines are tight; take a look at the<a href=\"https://strobesnmore.com/collections/horizontal-c-series-consoles\"> <span style=\"text-decoration:underline\">horizontal C Series consoles</span></a>.</p><p>Once the console is chosen, finish the build with<a href=\"https://strobesnmore.com/collections/console-accessories\"> <span style=\"text-decoration:underline\">console accessories</span></a> like internal cup holders, armrests, filler plates, and pole mounts to tailor the layout to your crew. Rounding out the cab with<a href=\"https://strobesnmore.com/collections/led-lights\"> <span style=\"text-decoration:underline\">LED warning lights</span></a> and, where needed,<a href=\"https://strobesnmore.com/collections/bumpers-partitions\"> <span style=\"text-decoration:underline\">push bumpers and partitions</span></a>, turns a bare vehicle into a fully equipped, field-ready unit.</p><h2>Why Buy Your Consoles From Strobes N' More</h2><p>Strobes N' More has spent years helping agencies and fleet managers build reliable in-vehicle command centers. We carry trusted brands like Havis, back every order with expert phone support at (401) 454-4487, and stock consoles for both current and legacy vehicle platforms so you're not stuck when you run an older cruiser. Whether you're outfitting a single patrol car or spec'ing an entire fleet, we help you match the right console, mounts, and accessories to the vehicle you actually drive.</p><p>Ready to upgrade your cab? Browse the full vehicle consoles collection above, or reach out and we'll build a package around your platform, your equipment, and your budget.</p>",
        "heading_size": "medium",
        "text_alignment": "left"
      }
    },
